
Use app1.py file

For Windows:
Save your Python script as a .py file, e.g., process_tracker.py.

Open Task Scheduler.

Create a new task:

General tab: Set a name and description for the task.
Triggers tab: Create a new trigger for "At log on" to run the task when the user logs in.
Actions tab: Create a new action for "Start a program" and browse to the location of your Python executable (e.g., C:\Path\To\python.exe) and set the arguments to the path of your script (e.g., C:\Path\To\process_tracker.py).
Save and run the task.
